   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "wRMtsJKBaxWu"
   },
   "source": [
    "## About the dataset\n",
    "Explain what the data is in your own words. What are your features and labels? What is the mapping of your labels to the actual classes?\\\n",
    "\\\n",
    "This dataset includes information on Iris plants and their various characteristics. In this case we are given four metrics as features (sepal length, sepal width, petal length, and petal width) and we want to predict the label of species. There are three classes of species here, Iris-Setosa, Iris-Versicolour, and Iris-Virginica. The classes are mapped to 1, 2, and 3 respectively in the code below."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "DhKaIrZKNaHg"
   },
   "source": [
    "# Part 2: Split the dataset into train and test"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {
    "colab": {
     "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
    },
    "id": "OrgogB62NcOi",
    "outputId": "7bbfb1ea-88ed-4944-ab94-48696b9a71df"
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Training size: 540\n",
      "Testing size: 60\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Map species to a number\n",
    "mapping ={\n",
    "    'setosa': 1,\n",
    "    'versicolor': 2,\n",
    "    'virginica': 3\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "data['species_encoded'] = data['species'].map(mapping)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Take the dataset and split it into our features (X) and label (y)\n",
    "x = data.drop(columns=['species_encoded', 'species'])\n",
    "y = data['species_encoded']\n",
    "\n",
    "# Use sklearn to split the features and labels into a training/test set. (90% train, 10% test)\n",
    "x_train, x_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(x, y, test_size=0.1, random_state=42)\n",
    "print(f'Training size: {x_train.size}')\n",
    "print(f'Testing size: {x_test.size}')\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "hblF-ei9Ncia"
   },
   "source": [
